  "_doc": "Phase-5c demo: REG_FILE (single-port read) and REG_FILE_DP (dual-port read), each with one synchronous write port. Click VERILOG to see how memory arrays land in Verilog: a single `reg [W-1:0] regs_<id> [0:DEPTH-1];` declaration, async read via `assign rd_data = regs[rd_addr];`, synchronous write inside `always @(posedge clk) if (we) regs[wr_addr] <= wr_data;`. The IR gained a new `Index` expression node (renders `name[idx]`) and a memory-array declaration path (`out.memories` from translators flows into `ir.memories`, rendered as the canonical Verilog memory decl). Both forms parse cleanly with iverilog.",
